NAME: ADDRESS
TITLE: Branch Address
DEFINITION: Street address at which the branch is physically located.

NAME: BKCLASS
TITLE: Institution Class
DEFINITION: A classification code assigned by the FDIC based on the institution's charter type (commercial bank or savings institution), charter agent (state or federal), Federal Reserve membership status (Fed member, Fed nonmember) and its primary federal regulator (state chartered institutions are subject to both federal and state supervision).

TITLE: N -
DEFINITION: Commercial bank, national (federal) charter and Fed member, supervised by the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC)

TITLE: NM -
DEFINITION: Commercial bank, state charter and Fed nonmember, supervised by the FDIC

TITLE: OI -
DEFINITION: Insured U.S. branch of a foreign chartered institution (IBA)

TITLE: SA -
DEFINITION: Savings associations, state or federal charter, supervised by the Office of Thrift Supervision (OTS)

TITLE: SB -
DEFINITION: Savings banks, state charter, supervised by the FDIC

TITLE: SM -
DEFINITION: Commercial bank, state charter and Fed member, supervised by the Federal Reserve (FRB)

NAME: CBSA
TITLE: Core Based Statistical Area Name (Branch)
DEFINITION: Name of the Core Based Statistical Area (CBSA) as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget.

NAME: CBSA_DIV
TITLE: Metropolitan Divisions Name (Branch)
DEFINITION: Name of the Core Based Statistical Division as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget.

NAME: CBSA_DIV_FLG
TITLE: Metropolitan Divisions Flag (Branch)
DEFINITION: A flag (1=Yes) indicating member of a Core Based Statistical Division as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget.

NAME: CBSA_DIV_NO
TITLE: Metropolitan Divisions Number (Branch)
DEFINITION: Numeric code of the Core Based Statistical Division as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget.

NAME: CBSA_METRO
TITLE: Metropolitan Division Number (Branch)
DEFINITION: Numeric code of the Metropolitan Statistical Area as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CBSA_METRO_FLG
TITLE: Metropolitan Division Flag (Branch)
DEFINITION: A flag (1=Yes) used to indicate whether an branch is in a Metropolitan Statistical Area as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CBSA_METRO_NAME
TITLE: Metropolitan Division Name (Branch)
DEFINITION: Name of the Metropolitan Statistical Area as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CBSA_MICRO_FLG
TITLE: Micropolitan Division Flag (Branch)
DEFINITION: A flag (1=Yes) used to indicate whether an branch is in a Micropolitan Statistical Area as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CBSA_NO
TITLE: Core Based Statistical Areas (Branch)
DEFINITION: Numeric code of the Core Based Statistical Area (CBSA) as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget.

NAME: CERT
TITLE: Institution FDIC Certificate #
DEFINITION: A unique number assigned by the FDIC used to identify institutions and for the issuance of insurance certificates.

NAME: CITY
TITLE: Branch City
DEFINITION: City in which branch is physically located.

NAME: COUNTY
TITLE: Branch County
DEFINITION: County where the branch is physically located.

NAME: CSA
TITLE: Combined Statistical Area Name (Branch)
DEFINITION: Name of the Combined Statistical Area (CSA) as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CSA_FLG
TITLE: Combined Statistical Area Flag  (Branch)
DEFINITION: Flag (1=Yes) indicating member of a Combined Statistical Area (CSA) as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: CSA_NO
TITLE: Combined Statistical Area Number  (Branch)
DEFINITION: Numeric code of the Combined Statistical Area (CSA) as defined by the US Census Bureau Office of Management and Budget

NAME: ESTYMD
TITLE: Branch Established Date
DEFINITION: The date on which the branch began operations.

NAME: FI_UNINUM
TITLE: FDIC UNINUM of the Owner Institution
DEFINITION: This is the FDIC UNINUM of the institution that owns the branch.  A UNINUM is a unique sequentially number added to the FDIC database for both banks and  branches.  There is no pattern imbedded within the number.  The FI_UNINUM is updated with every merger or purchase of branches to reflect the most current owner.

NAME: MAINOFF
TITLE: Main Office
DEFINITION: The main office for the institution.

NAME: NAME
TITLE: Institution Name
DEFINITION: Legal name of the FDIC Insured Institution

NAME: OFFNAME
TITLE: Office Name
DEFINITION: Name of the branch.

NAME: OFFNUM
TITLE: Branch Number
DEFINITION: The branch's corresponding office number.

NAME: RUNDATE
TITLE: Run Date
DEFINITION: The day the institution information was updated.

NAME: SERVTYPE
TITLE: Service Type Code
DEFINITION: Define the various types of offices of FDIC-insured institutions.
Full Service Brick and Mortar Office
Full Service Retail Office
Full Service Cyber Office
Full Service Mobile Office
Full Service Home/Phone Banking
Full Service Seasonal Office
Limited Service Administrative Office
Limited Service Military Facility
Limited Service Facility Office
Limited Service Loan Production Office
Limited Service Consumer Credit Office
Limited Service Contractual Office
Limited Service Messenger Office
Limited Service Retail Office
Limited Service Mobile Office
Limited Service Trust Office

NAME: STALP
TITLE: Branch State Abbreviation
DEFINITION: State abbreviation in which the branch is physically located. The FDIC Act defines state as any State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any territory of the United States, Puerto Rico, Guam, American Samoa, the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands, the Virgin Island, and the Northern Mariana Islands.

NAME: STCNTY
TITLE: State and County Number
DEFINITION: A five digit number representing the state and county in which the institution is physically located.  The first two digits represent the FIPS state numeric code and the last three digits represent the FIPS county numeric code.

NAME: STNAME
TITLE: Branch State
DEFINITION: State in which the  branch is physically located. The FDIC Act defines state as any State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any territory of the United States, Puerto Rico, Guam, American Samoa, the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands, the Virgin Island, and the Northern Mariana Islands.

NAME: UNINUM
TITLE: Unique Identification Number for a Branch Office
DEFINITION: Unique Identification Number for a Branch Office as assigned by the FDIC

NAME: ZIP
TITLE: Branch Zip Code
DEFINITION: The first five digits of the full postal zip code representing physical location of the branch.
